    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "Inland\nAIR LInes\nJUN 13 1939\nMt. Rushmore\nS VACATION LAND",
      "Inland AIR LInEs\nSEATTLE\nTACOMA\nPORTLAND\nVANCOUVER\nSANAUL\nGLACIER FK:\nSPOKANE\nFRANCISCO\nSACRAMENTO\nOAKLAND\nSALT LAKE\nGREAT FALLS\nLEWIS TOWN\nBILLINGS\nSHERIDAN\nCASPER\nCHEYENNE\nBLACK HILLS\nFARGO\nPIÈRRE\nHURON\nRAPID\nCITY\nОМАНА\nDENVER\n• COLORADO SPRINGS\nTWIN\nCITIES\nNEW YORK\nPHILADELPHIA\nCAMDEN\nWASHINGTON\nSI LOUIS\nKANSAS\nLOS ANGELES\nSAN DIEGO\n• To Mexico City\nTo Mexico City, Central and South An\nTo Cuba, Central and\nTime is important.\nFly\nthe safe, speedy, economical In-\nland Air Lines and be sure of arriving at your destination first.\nYou'll welcome the comfort,\nconvenience, and friendly\nWestern spirit that distinguishes Inland Air Lines service. You'll\napreciate the safety of Inland's powerful, twin-motored Boeing\nplanes, and Inland's\nhighly-trained,\nexperienced,\nand thor-\noughly capable personnel.\nYou'll enjoy the magnificent scen-\nery of the Western vacationland over which Inland Skyways\nwill take you.\nAnd most of all, you will be convinced that Inland's Spe-\ncial Round Trip Fares offer you the fastest, safest, most\ncon-\nvenient and economical travel for your year round business\nand pleasure trips.\nAIR MAIL « AIR EXPRESS « PASSENGERS",
      "Inland\nAIR LInes\n13360\nBOBING\nJUNE 1, 1939\nSERVING AMERICA"
    ],
